{"key":"processedPost-16137133","value":{"id":16137133,"first":16137106,"last":27735074,"when":1335361714,"utime":"04/25/12 04:48 PM","content":"Try harvesting the correct way.&nbsp; You're supposed to cut the stem off at the base with a sharp knife, leaving the stem butt firmly attached to the substrate.&nbsp; This leaves no substrate on the stem, and what little might have splashed up during misting easily brushes off after the fruit is dry by using a stiff paint or tooth brush.<br /><br />Don't destroy your mycelium by ripping a large chunk of it out when harvesting.&nbsp; This improper process destroys more outdoor patches than any other thing people do and it's even worse on indoor grows.<br />RR","title":"Re: How do you deal with substrate on the shroom base after harvesting?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}